detail.target:
1. An endoscope processor comprising:
a power supply circuit;
an endoscope connection portion;
a discharge resistor disposed between the power supply circuit and the endoscope connection portion;
a power conduction circuit disposed between the discharge resistor and the endoscope connection portion;
an endoscope connection detection unit configured to detect that an endoscope has been connected to the endoscope connection portion; and
a control unit connected to the endoscope connection detection unit and configured to control the power supply circuit,
wherein the control unit, in response to detection by the detection unit that the endoscope has changed from a disconnected state to a connected state, brings the power conduction circuit into a conductive state to electrically connect the endoscope and the discharge resistor, thereby discharging electric charge accumulated in the endoscope through the discharge resistor of the endoscope processor, and then, upon supplying power to the endoscope from the power supply circuit, renders the endoscope and the discharge resistor non-conductive by means of the power conduction circuit.
